(1411, 'Publish', '2010-09-30 02:27:51', '2014-07-29 19:09:27', 'Mammals', 'EDGE', '91', 'Mammalia', 'Pholidota', 'Manidae', 'Manis pentadactyla', '', 'Chinese Pangolin', '20.35572093', 'EN', '5.14076120', '<p>Pangolin in Cantonese is &ldquo;Chun-shua-cap&rdquo; which means &ldquo;scaly hill-borer&rdquo;. This refers to the Chinese legend that pangolins travel all around the world underground</p>', 'In Chinese legend pangolins are said to travel all around the world underground, and in the Cantonese language the name for pangolins translates to “the animal that digs through the mountain,” or “Chun-shua-cap,” which translates to “scaly hill-borer.”', '', 'Limited', 'N', 'N', 'Bangladesh; Bhutan; China; Hong Kong; India; Lao People''s Democratic Republic; Myanmar; Nepal; Taiwan, Province of China; Thailand; Viet Nam', '', ''),
