(1408, 'Publish', '2010-09-30 02:27:51', '2010-11-19 14:14:36', 'Mammals', 'EDGE', '62', 'Mammalia', 'Chiroptera', 'Hipposideridae', 'Hipposideros lamottei', '', 'Lamotte''s Roundleaf Bat', '11.87525960', 'CR', '5.32789633', 'These bats are believed to fly with their mouths closed, emitting ultrasonic pulses their elaborately modified noses.', 'As is suggested by the name, this species is characterized by elaborate modifications of the nose and muzzle, forming leaf-like projections that are thought to help focus echolocation signals emitted through the nose.', '', 'None', 'N', 'N', 'Guinea', '', ''),
(1406, 'Publish', '2010-09-30 02:27:51', '2012-04-13 11:31:06', 'Mammals', 'EDGE', '47', 'Mammalia', 'Primates', 'Lemuridae', 'Hapalemur alaotrensis', 'Hapalemur griseus ssp. Alaotrensis', 'Lake Alaotra Gentle Lemur', '13.49001975', 'CR', '5.44604884', 'The only primate confined to wetlands, this species is found exclusively around Madagascar’s largest lake - Lac Alaotra.', 'H. alaotrensis is the only primate in the world whose habitat is confined to wetlands and is found exclusively in the papyrus and reed beds surrounding Madagascar’s largest lake - Lac Alaotra.', 'Alaotra Reed Lemur, Alaotran Gentle Lemur, Lac Alaotra Bamboo Lemur, ', 'Active', 'N', 'N', 'Madagascar', '', ''),
