(1952, 'Publish', '2014-03-27 10:31:43', '2014-04-23 17:00:35', 'Birds', 'EDGE', '41', 'Aves', 'Charadriiformes', 'Glareolidae', 'Rhinoptilus bitorquatus', 'Cursorius bitorquatus', 'Jerdon’s Courser', '11.857601\r\n', 'CR', '5.326524\r\n', 'The species was thought to be extinct until it was rediscovered in 1986, over 85 years after the last record.', 'Very little is known about this enigmatic courser, which spent 85 years of the 20th century eluding researchers. Population estimates place numbers between 50 and 249 mature individuals the species is classified as critically endangered.', 'Double-banded Courser', 'Active', 'N', 'N', 'India', NULL, NULL),
(1953, 'Publish', '2014-03-27 10:31:43', '2014-03-27 10:31:43', 'Birds', 'EDGE', '78', 'Aves', 'Falconiformes (or Accipitriformes)', 'Accipitridae', 'Haliaeetus vociferoides', NULL, 'Madagascar Fish-eagle', '8.419427\r\n', 'CR', '5.015363\r\n', 'The largest bird of prey in Madagascar, this beautiful endemic fish-eagle is on the verge of extinction.', 'This large fish-eagle, numbers at approximately 240 adults in the wild. The nature of its diet means it comes into direct competition with local fishermen, who shoot the bird or take nestlings in an attempt to preserve fish stocks.', 'Madagascan Fish Eagle, Madagascar Fish Eagle, Madagascar Sea Eagle, Ankoay (local name)', 'Active', 'N', 'N', 'Madagascar', NULL, NULL),
(1954, 'Publish', '2014-03-27 10:31:43', '2014-03-27 10:31:43', 'Birds', 'EDGE', '76', 'Aves', 'Charadriiformes', 'Charadriidae', 'Thinornis novaeseelandiae', 'Charadrius novaeseelandiae, Charadrius dudoroa, Charadrius torquatula, Hiaticula novaeseelandiae, Thinornis novae-seelandiae, Thinoriss rossii, Charadrius atricinctus,', 'Shore Plover', '17.883186\r\n', 'EN', '5.017713\r\n', 'One of the rarest plovers in the world, the Shore Plover is now restricted to a small number of islands around New Zealand.', 'This stocky little wader is one of the world’s rarest and most endangered coastal birds. The Shore Plover was once widespread down the southern coast of the South Island of New Zealand. Today it is restricted to a small number of off-shore islands.', 'Sand plover, New Zealand Plover, New Zealand Shore Plover, Shore Dotterel, Tuturuatu.', 'Active', 'N', 'N', 'New Zealand', NULL, NULL),
(1955, 'Publish', '2014-03-27 10:31:44', '2014-03-27 10:31:44', 'Birds', 'EDGE', '49', 'Aves', 'Charadriiformes', 'Charadriidae', 'Vanellus gregarius', NULL, 'Sociable Lapwing', '10.708931\r\n', 'CR', '5.232941\r\n', 'The Sociable Lapwing was so-called following observations of birds gathering in large migratory flocks.', 'This species is a steppe specialist and was once widespread across the vast grasslands that stretch from eastern Ukraine to the Altai mountains. Numbers today are a fraction of the historical population and the Sociable Lapwing is now Critically Endangered.', 'Sociable plover', 'Active', 'N', '', 'Afghanistan; Armenia; Azerbaijan; Cameroon; Central African Republic; Chad; Eritrea; Ethiopia; Georgia; India; Iran, Islamic Republic of; Iraq; Israel; Jordan; Kazakhstan; Kyrgyzstan; Lebanon; Oman; Pakistan; Palestinian Territory, Occupied; Qatar; Russian Federation; Saudi Arabia; Sri Lanka; Sudan; Syrian Arab Republic; Tajikistan; Turkey; Turkmenistan; United Arab Emirates; Uzbekistan', NULL, NULL),
