(1958, 'Publish', '2014-03-27 10:55:28', '2014-04-27 13:59:41', 'Birds', 'EDGE', '30', 'Aves', 'Falconiformes (or Accipitriformes)', 'Accipitridae', 'Neophron percnopterus', NULL, 'Egyptian Vulture', '27.712059\r\n', 'EN', '5.436759\r\n', 'This long-lived, intelligent bird has experienced catastrophic population crashes worldwide.', 'This species has a huge global range with populations found in southern Europe, Middle East, India and northern and eastern Africa. This intelligent and distinctive, white vulture is in decline due to an array of threats, including poisoning, poaching, electrocution and human disturbance.', 'White Scavenger Vulture, Pharaoh''s Chicken', 'Active', 'N', '', 'Afghanistan; Albania; Algeria; Andorra; Angola; Armenia; Azerbaijan; Benin; Bosnia and Herzegovina; Bulgaria; Burkina Faso; Cameroon; Cape Verde; Central African Republic; Chad; China; Cote d''Ivoire; Croatia; Cyprus; Djibouti; Egypt; Eritrea; Ethiopia; France; Gambia; Georgia; Ghana; Gibraltar; Greece; Guinea; Guinea-Bissau; India; Iran, Islamic Republic of; Iraq; Israel; Italy; Jordan; Kazakhstan; Kenya; Kuwait; Kyrgyzstan; Lebanon; Libya; Macedonia, the former Yugoslav Republic of; Mali; Malta; Mauritania; Moldova; Montenegro; Morocco; Namibia; Nepal; Niger; Nigeria; Oman; Pakistan; Palestinian Territory, Occupied; Portugal; Romania; Russian Federation; Saudi Arabia; Senegal; Serbia; Somalia; South Africa; South Sudan; Spain; Sudan; Syrian Arab Republic; Tajikistan; Tanzania, United Republic of; Togo; Tunisia; Turkey; Turkmenistan; Uganda; Ukraine; United Arab Emirates; Uzbekistan; Western Sahara; Yemen; Zimbabwe', NULL, NULL),
(1965, 'Publish', '2014-03-27 11:01:27', '2014-03-27 11:01:27', 'Birds', 'EDGE', '68', 'Aves', 'Gruiformes', 'Rallidae', 'Gallinula silvestris', 'Edithornis silvestris, Pareudiasles silvestris, Gallinula sylvestris, Gallinula sylvestris sylvestris', 'Makira Moorhen', '9.054193\r\n', 'CR', '5.080579\r\n', 'This moorhen has not been seen since 1953. Urgent research is required to discover if the species can still be saved from extinction.', 'The Makira Moorhen is found on only one island in the Solomon Islands. The last sighting occurred over 50 years ago and it has eluded researchers ever since. Tantalising reports from local villagers keep hopes alive that species still exists.', 'Makira Woodhen, San Cristobal Moorhen, San Cristobal Mountain Rail', 'Limited', 'Y', '', 'Solomon Islands', NULL, NULL),
(1966, 'Publish', '2014-03-27 11:01:27', '2014-04-23 10:03:17', 'Birds', 'EDGE', '12', 'Aves', 'Ciconiiformes', 'Threskiornithidae', 'Geronticus eremita', NULL, 'Northern Bald Ibis', '19.508976\r\n', 'CR', '5.793451\r\n', 'This red-faced ibis has suffered a rapid decline in numbers over the last few decades and is now Critically Endangered.', 'This distinctive, red-faced bird was once widespread across Northern Africa and Europe. With the global population in the wild now estimated at just over 200 breeding wild adults essentially confined to just two sites in Morocco, the species is listed as Critically Endangered. There are also semi-wild populations in Turkey (~150 birds) and more than 2000 individuals in captivity.', 'Hermit Ibis, Waldrapp Ibis, Bare-faced Ibis, Red faced Ibis, Bald Ibis', 'Active', 'N', '', 'Algeria; Eritrea; Jordan; Iraq; Mauritania; Morocco; Saudi Arabia; Syrian Arab Republic; Turkey; Yemen', NULL, NULL),
