(1972, 'Publish', '2014-03-27 11:02:29', '2014-03-27 11:02:29', 'Birds', 'EDGE', '93', 'Aves', 'Trogoniformes', 'Trogonidae', 'Apalharpactes reinwardtii', 'Harpactes reinwardtii', 'Javan Trogon', '15.922912\r\n', 'EN', '4.90811\r\n', 'This beautiful, brightly-coloured bird is restricted to six forested mountains in western Java, Indonesia.', 'This endemic trogon is highly elusive, despite its conspicuous brightly-coloured plumage. It spends most of its time foraging in the lower storey of montane rainforest in western Java, Indonesia.', 'Reinwardt’s Blue-tailed Trogon', 'Limited', 'N', 'N', 'Indonesia', NULL, NULL),
(1974, 'Publish', '2014-03-27 11:02:29', '2014-04-10 16:08:01', 'Birds', 'EDGE', '42', 'Aves', 'Gruiformes Family: Otididae', NULL, 'Sypheotides indicus', 'Sypheotis aurita, Eupodotis indica, Sypheotides indica', 'Lesser Florican', '24.273878\r\n', 'EN', '5.309213\r\n', 'This black and white little florican is best known for the male’s elaborate, aerial courtship displays.', 'An iconic Indian bird, the Lesser Florican is best known for the male’s aerial courtship displays, which he uses to attract local females. Hunting, habitat loss and erratic monsoon seasons have caused the dramatic decline in numbers.', 'Likh', 'Active', 'N', '', 'India; Nepal; Pakistan', NULL, NULL),
(1979, 'Publish', '2014-03-27 11:04:50', '2014-03-27 11:04:50', 'Birds', 'EDGE', '57', 'Aves', 'Gruiformes', 'Psophiidae', 'Psophia viridis', 'Psophia viridis viridis, Psophia viridis dextralis, Psophia viridis obscura, Psophia viridis interjecta', 'Dark-winged Trumpeter', '20.168346\r\n', 'EN', '5.131948\r\n', 'Endemic to the rainforests of the Brazilian Amazon, the Dark-winged Trumpeter may actually be three different species.', 'This elusive trumpeter can be found in four Amazonian interfluves (areas separated by major rivers). These four different populations have previously been assigned to three (or four) different subspecies, but the latest studies indicate that they would be better treated as three (or four) different species.', 'Green-winged Trumpeter', 'Limited', 'N', '', 'Bolivia, Plurinational State of; Brazil', NULL, NULL),
(1980, 'Publish', '2014-03-27 11:05:34', '2014-03-27 11:05:34', 'Birds', 'EDGE', '65', 'Aves', 'Psittaciformes', 'Psittacidae', 'Nestor meridionalis', 'Psittacus hypopolius, Psittacus meridionalis', 'Kaka', '19.39575\r\n', 'EN', '5.094768\r\n', 'Native to New Zealand, the inquisitive and vocal Kaka has evolved into two subspecies, one on each of the main islands.', 'At first glance, this inquisitive parrot appears to have brown, drab plumage. However, this belies the beautiful, crimson underwings that are exposed in flight. Native to New Zealand, the Kaka has evolved into two subspecies, one on each of the main islands.', 'Common Kaka, New Zealand Kaka', 'Active', 'N', 'N', 'New Zealand', NULL, NULL),
(1981, 'Publish', '2014-03-27 11:07:54', '2014-04-10 13:30:55', 'Birds', 'EDGE', '95', 'Aves', 'Passeriformes', 'Thamnophilidae', 'Myrmotherula snowi', 'Myrmotherula unicolor', 'Alagoas Antwren', '7.407455\r\n', 'CR', '4.901708\r\n', 'With an estimated surviving population of just 30 to 200 adults, this critically endangered antwren may soon be extinct.', 'Extensive clearance of lowland areas of the Atlantic Forest has caused the range of this species to contract to upland habitat. With an estimated surviving population of just 30 to 200 adults, this antwren may soon be extinct.', NULL, 'Active', 'N', 'N', 'Brazil', NULL, NULL),
(1982, 'Publish', '2014-03-27 11:20:27', '2014-04-23 11:11:06', 'Birds', 'EDGE', '18', 'Aves', 'Cuculiformes', 'Cuculidae', 'Centropus steerii', NULL, 'Black-hooded Coucal', '15.252189\r\n', 'CR', '5.560816\r\n', 'This critically endangered cuckoo spends most of it time in dense, tangled vegetation in the primary forests of Mindoro Island in the Philippines.', 'Endemic to the island of Mindoro in the Philippines, this cuckoo is critically endangered due to severe and rapid habitat loss. Almost all the primary forest on the island has been eradicated with the remaining tracts predicted to disappear within the next 20 years.', 'Steere''s Coucal', 'Active', 'N', 'N', 'Philippines', NULL, NULL),
