(2030, 'Publish', '2014-03-27 12:53:22', '2014-04-07 17:21:43', 'Birds', 'EDGE', '79', 'Aves', 'Pelecaniformes', 'Ardeidae', 'Ardea insignis', 'Ardea imperialis, Ardea imperialis imperialis', 'White-bellied Heron', '8.402338\r\n', 'CR', '5.013547\r\n', 'Standing over a metre in height, the White-bellied Heron is the second largest heron in the world.', 'This large, distinctive heron, with its long slender neck, stands over a metre tall. A solitary species, it spends most of its time along the rivers and lakes of Bhutan, India and Myanmar. There are estimated to be fewer than 250 individuals left in the world.', 'Great White-bellied Heron, Imperial Heron, White Bellied Heron', 'Active', 'N', 'N', 'Bangladesh; Bhutan; India; Myanmar', NULL, NULL),
